.TH VARC 1 "December 2025" "0.3.27" "VaultArchive Manual"
.SH NAME
varc \- file archiving utility
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B varc
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fICOMMAND\fR [\fIARCHIVE\fR] [\fIFILES...\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B VaultArchive
is a secure file archiving utility that creates, extracts, and manages compressed and encrypted archives.
It supports multiple files and directories in a single archive file with AES-256 encryption and zlib compression.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
\fBcreate\fR, \fBc\fR, \fBpack\fR
Create a new archive file
.TP
\fBextract\fR, \fBx\fR, \fBunpack\fR
Extract files from an archive
.TP
\fBlist\fR, \fBl\fR
List archive contents
.TP
\fBverify\fR, \fBv\fR
Verify archive integrity
.TP
\fBadd\fR, \fa\fR
Add files to an existing archive
.TP
\fBremove\fR, \fBrm\fR
Remove files from an archive
.TP
\fBlock\fR
Encrypt/lock an archive with a password
.TP
\fBunlock\fR
Decrypt/unlock an archive
.TP
\fBhelp\fR
Show help information
.TP
\fBversion\fR
Show version information
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-help\fR, \fB\-h\fR
Show help message and exit
.TP
\fB\-\-version\fR, \fB\-v\fR
Show version information and exit
.TP
\fB\-\-password\fR, \fB\-p\fR \fI<PASSWORD>\fR
Specify password for encryption/decryption
.TP
\fB\-\-encrypt\fR, \fB\-e\fR
Enable encryption for the archive
.TP
\fB\-\-no-compress\fR
Disable compression
.TP
\fB\-\-compress-level\fR \fI<0-9>\fR
Set compression level (0=none, 1=fastest, 6=default, 9=best)
.TP
\fB\-\-overwrite\fR, \fB\-o\fR
Overwrite existing files
.TP
\fB\-\-quiet\fR, \fB\-q\fR
Suppress progress output
.TP
\fB\-\-raw\fR
Raw output without formatting
.SH FILE FORMAT
.B VARC
archive files use the following structure:
.TP
Header (64 bytes)
Contains magic signature, version, flags, file count, and cryptographic parameters
.TP
Entry Headers
Metadata for each file including path, size, and type
.TP
Data
Compressed and/or encrypted file data
.TP
Checksums
SHA-256 hashes for integrity verification
.SH ENCRYPTION
By default, archives use AES-256-CBC encryption with PBKDF2-HMAC-SHA256 key derivation.
The default iteration count is 100,000 (OWASP recommended minimum).
.SH EXAMPLES
Create an archive:
.RS
.B varc create backup.varc ./documents
.RE
.PP
Create an encrypted archive:
.RS
.B varc create \-\-encrypt \-\-password mypass backup.varc ./files
.RE
.PP
Extract an archive:
.RS
.B varc extract backup.varc ./output
.RE
.PP
List archive contents:
.RS
.B varc list backup.varc
.RE
.PP
Verify archive integrity:
.RS
.B varc verify \-\-password mypass secure.varc
.RE
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
VARCPASSWORD
Can be set to avoid prompting for password (not recommended for security)
